<h3 class='page-header'>Import Licensees</h3>

<div class='card bg-dark col-10 rounded mb-2 shadow mx-auto border-info'>
  <h4 class='page-header'>Reminders</h4>
  <div class='card-body text-white p-4'>
    <ul>
      <li>The application will read your spreadsheet and attempt to find the 
          object by its ID, then update the record (if the ID exists) or create a new 
          record (if the ID does not exist yet).</li>
      <li>Do not change existing IDs. Add new IDs in chronological order. Do not
          reassign IDs of previously deleted records.</li>
      <li>Only import spreadsheets that were previously downloaded from this 
          application; others cannot be read correctly.</li>
      <li>Always import licensees before importing placements.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>


<div class='card bg-dark col-10 rounded mb-2 shadow mx-auto border-info'>
  <h4 class='page-header'>Select File</h4>
  <div class='card-body text-white'>
    <%= form_for @licensees_import do |f| %>
      <% if @licensees_import.errors.any? %>
        <%= pluralize(@licensees_import.errors.count, "error") %> prevented us from
        importing your spreadsheet. Please update your spreadsheet and try again.
        <ul>
          <% @licensees_import.errors.full_messages.each do |msg| %>
            <li><%= msg %></li>
          <% end %>
        </ul>
      <% end %>

      <%= f.file_field :file %>
      <%= f.submit "Import File" %>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</div>

<div class='text-center'>
    <%= link_to "Back", :back, class: 'btn btn-standard' %>
</div>